						<div class="postbody">I use the A, X, and Y registers first, but also have zero page variables that simulate MIPS registers:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;.org $0000<br />a0:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;; argument registers<br />a1:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />a2:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />a3:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />a4:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />a5:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t0:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;; temporary registers<br />t1:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t2:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t3:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t4:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t5:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t6:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t7:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t8:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />t9:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />s0:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;; save registers<br />s1:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />s2:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />s3:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />s4:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />s5:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;<br />v0:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;; return value registers<br />v1:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;&nbsp; (or more arguments)<br />i0:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;; temporary registers<br />i1:&nbsp; &nbsp;.db 0&nbsp; &nbsp;;&nbsp; (for interrupts)<br /></div></div>

